.Dd March 28, 2026
.Dt CACL 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm cacl
.Nd Capability Access Control List device
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/ioctl.h
.In cacl.h
.Pp
.Fd #include <fcntl.h>
.Ft int
.Fn open "/dev/cacl" "O_RDWR"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
device provides a mechanism for attaching Access Control Lists (ACLs)
to file descriptors.
When an ACL is attached to a descriptor, only processes whose tokens
appear in the ACL may perform operations on that descriptor.
.Pp
Each process has a unique 64-bit token that is randomly generated at
.Xr exec 2 .
Tokens are inherited across
.Xr fork 2
but change on
.Xr exec 2 ,
providing compartmentalization for sandboxed child processes.
.Pp
ACL entries are automatically cleaned up when no process holds the
associated token (all have exited or called
.Xr exec 2 ) .
.Ss Supported Descriptor Types
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Pipes
.Pq Xr pipe 2
.It
Sockets
.Pq Xr socket 2 , Xr socketpair 2
.It
POSIX shared memory
.Pq Xr shm_open 2
.It
Regular files and FIFOs
.Pq Xr open 2
.El
.Ss ACL States
A descriptor can be in one of three states:
.Bl -tag -width "default-allow"
.It Em default-allow
No ACL attached.
All processes may access the descriptor.
This is the initial state.
.It Em ACL active
An ACL is attached with one or more entries.
Only processes with matching tokens may access the descriptor.
.It Em locked
The ACL is locked (deny-all mode).
No processes may access the descriptor regardless of token.
.El
.Sh IOCTLS
The following
.Xr ioctl 2
commands are supported on the
.Pa /dev/cacl
device:
.Bl -tag -width CACL_IOC_ADD_SELF_TIMED
.It Dv CACL_IOC_ADD
Add processes (by process descriptor) to access lists.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_members
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_ADD_SELF
Add the calling process to access lists.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_fds
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_REMOVE
Remove processes (by process descriptor) from access lists.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_members
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_REMOVE_SELF
Remove the calling process from access lists.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_fds
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_CLEAR
Clear all entries from access lists, returning to default-allow.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_fds
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_LOCK
Lock access lists in deny-all mode.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_fds
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_QUERY
Query if a process is in an access list.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_query
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_COUNT
Count entries in an access list.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_count
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_ADD_TIMED
Add processes with expiry timeout.
Entries are removed after the specified seconds OR when no process
holds the token.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_members_timed
argument.
.It Dv CACL_IOC_ADD_SELF_TIMED
Add the calling process with expiry timeout.
Takes a
.Vt struct cacl_fds_timed
argument.
.El
.Sh DATA STRUCTURES
.Bd -literal
struct cacl_members {
    int      *cm_cap_fds;     /* descriptors to modify */
    uint16_t  cm_cap_count;   /* number of descriptors */
    int      *cm_proc_fds;    /* process descriptors */
    uint16_t  cm_proc_count;  /* number of processes */
};

struct cacl_fds {
    int      *cf_cap_fds;     /* descriptors to modify */
    uint16_t  cf_cap_count;   /* number of descriptors */
};

struct cacl_query {
    int       cq_cap_fd;      /* descriptor to check */
    int       cq_proc_fd;     /* process to check */
    int       cq_result;      /* output: 1=member, 0=not */
};

struct cacl_count {
    int       cc_cap_fd;      /* descriptor to query */
    uint32_t  cc_count;       /* output: entry count */
    int       cc_locked;      /* output: 1=locked, 0=not */
};

struct cacl_members_timed {
    int      *cmt_cap_fds;    /* descriptors to modify */
    uint16_t  cmt_cap_count;  /* number of descriptors */
    int      *cmt_proc_fds;   /* process descriptors */
    uint16_t  cmt_proc_count; /* number of processes */
    uint32_t  cmt_timeout_sec;/* expiry in seconds */
};

struct cacl_fds_timed {
    int      *cft_cap_fds;    /* descriptors to modify */
    uint16_t  cft_cap_count;  /* number of descriptors */
    uint32_t  cft_timeout_sec;/* expiry in seconds */
};
.Ed
.Sh EXAMPLES
Add the calling process to a pipe's ACL:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#include <sys/ioctl.h>
#include <fcntl.h>
#include "cacl.h"

int cacl_fd, pipe_fd;
struct cacl_fds cf;

cacl_fd = open("/dev/cacl", O_RDWR);
cf.cf_cap_fds = &pipe_fd;
cf.cf_cap_count = 1;
ioctl(cacl_fd, CACL_IOC_ADD_SELF, &cf);
.Ed
.Pp
Add a child process with 60-second timeout:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
struct cacl_members_timed cmt;

cmt.cmt_cap_fds = &pipe_fd;
cmt.cmt_cap_count = 1;
cmt.cmt_proc_fds = &child_pfd;
cmt.cmt_proc_count = 1;
cmt.cmt_timeout_sec = 60;
ioctl(cacl_fd, CACL_IOC_ADD_TIMED, &cmt);
.Ed
.Sh SYSCTL VARIABLES
The following
.Xr sysctl 8
variables are available:
.Bl -tag -width "security.cacl.stat_auto_cleanups"
.It Va security.cacl.verbose
Enable verbose debug output (default: 0).
.It Va security.cacl.stat_acls_created
Number of ACLs created.
.It Va security.cacl.stat_entries_added
Number of entries added.
.It Va security.cacl.stat_entries_removed
Number of entries removed.
.It Va security.cacl.stat_auto_cleanups
Number of automatic cleanups performed.
.It Va security.cacl.stat_access_denied
Number of access denials.
.It Va security.cacl.stat_access_allowed
Number of access grants.
.El
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Nm
ioctls may fail with:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EBADF
A file descriptor argument is invalid.
.It Bq Er EINVAL
Invalid argument (e.g., NULL pointer, zero count).
.It Bq Er ENOMEM
Insufficient kernel memory.
.It Bq Er EPERM
Operation not permitted (e.g., adding to locked ACL).
.It Bq Er EOPNOTSUPP
Descriptor type not supported.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr capsicum 4 ,
.Xr mac 4 ,
.Xr pdfork 2 ,
.Xr ioctl 2
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
device first appeared in
.Fx 15.0 .
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm
module was written as an extension to Capsicum for fine-grained
access control on shared descriptors.
.Sh CAVEATS
.Bl -bullet
.It
Path-based operations
.Pq Xr open 2 , Xr stat 2
bypass ACL checks; use
.Xr cap_enter 2
to prevent path-based access.
.It
The
.Xr poll 2
and
.Xr select 2
system calls currently cannot be denied by ACLs.
.It
ACL entries are limited to 65536 per descriptor.
.El
